claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: Flow diagram illustrating the number of participants aged 18–64 who received recombinant vaccine versus standard-dose vaccine across the 2018–2021 seasons, with successive exclusions leading to final cohort sizes and age breakdowns. The figure is purely a participant flowchart detailing enrollment, exclusions, and cohort sizes; it contains no information on antigenic match or strain selection and therefore does not support the claim.
